/**
 * This test is done against the contract: Wallet.sol
 *
 * A very brief test on the fundamental aspects of consensus (root state, receipt hash, block hash)
 * to help us ensure that we are not doing something completely wrong.
 *
 * The second block sends off 8 transactions in it. The following scenarios are covered:
 * - Rejected transaction (invalid nonce)
 * - Failed transaction (out of energy)
 * - Value transfer only
 * - Successes on different calls
 *
 * If you believe you are modifying consensus-related aspects of the code that are more nuanced then
 * add the transactions that will exploit this and ideally add that transaction to the second block
 * of transactions.
 */
